4: I'm back... Um, what's going on?
12:
Woo-hoo! Welcome back! How ya
doing? All better?
15:
Yes, I'm fine... I apologize for my
mistake and any worry I caused.
18:
It's fine, you can save all that stuff
for later! And by that I mean, you
can write a formal apology some
other time!
21:
In order to better protect this
division, the chief asked for our help.
23:
No more secrets, hun. Everyone here
already knows what's going on.
26:
I apologize. I neglected to report the
extent of my work to you.
29:
Well, like she said, no more secrets.
From now on, we fight as a team!
32:
And I'm officially putting YOU in
charge of strategy! You're clearly an
expert at pulling the wool over
someone's eyes!
35:
All right... Looks like I better hop to it if
I want to redeem myself.
38:
Leave all the messy stuff to me.
Whatever your plan is, I'll make it
happen!
41:
Actually, you've got three
superweapons at your disposal, so
better make use of them!
45:
Uh... Not sure how I feel about being
called a superweapon.
57:
Hey there, can you hear me? I'm
cutting loose over here. Should I reel
it in?
59:
No, you're good to go! We're past the
point of no return.
60:
Just keep at it and back them into a
corner!
62:
You got it! And don't forget about
the preparations we discussed!
66:
This is a lot of enemies though... Just
how much do these guys hate you?
70:
Nyahaha. I guess being amazing
has its downsides. Not fair, right?
75:
Guys, they're bringing in
reinforcements! We have to fall
back!
78:
So you're the Tink I've heard so
much about. Ha, you sure pack a
punch, I'll give you that.
80:
But this is the last punch you'll throw.
It's time to put you out of
commission!
84:
I already looked into your
weaknesses. Tell me, did you ask
your company for permission to use
your Chip D'éclat? Hahaha!
90:
Turns out the old coot in my office
used to be one hell of an engineer.
And here I thought he was a janitor.
94:
Hijacking the control system of my
Chip D'éclat from the company was
a piece of cake-flavored AdTaste for
him.
97:
B-but attacking any targets outside
your objective should still violate
your company's policies! You can't
touch us—
99:
Noxel Group Bylaws, article
eighty-four, paragraph
three—Non-combatant personnel
may take up arms in circumstances
that meet the listed criteria.
100:
When it comes to legal affairs, I've
got your back... and then some.
102:
Chief, we've got our evidence! Blast
those bastards away!
105:
You know... I didn't really have any
beef with you.
108:
But once you laid a hand on my
team... That's when things got
personal.
111:
W-wait! I-I'm just a troubleshooter! I
was just doing my job, I swear!
118:
Chief! You didn't hit him, right?
Right?!
121:
Nyahaha, come on, have a little faith
in your boss, will ya? Of course I
didn't hit him. I did everything
according to plan.
125:
Phew... That takes care of the riffraff.
Are we done?
129:
That went pretty well, all things
considered. This must be what they
mean by teamwork makes the
dream work.
135:
Nyahaha! Who knew fighting as a
team would be so fun!
137:
Great job, everyone! We all did
GREAT!
142:
Chief... You're all right... Thank
goodness.
146:
Aww, cut it out. I'm the one who
should be worrying about you! Have
you finished your formal apology yet?
150:
Come on, give the guy a break. He's
the whole reason your team still
exists after that stunt.
153:
Well... Our department certainly
wasn't cut, but all of us workers are
now independent subcontractors
instead of full-time employees.
154:
I did my best, but unfortunately, that
was all I could do.
157:
Ha, sounds like a good deal to me.
You don't need that release code or
whatever anymore either, right?
162:
Right! I'm fuzzy on the details, but
the limiters on my Chip D'éclat are
gone! Guess those limiters had
something to do with being a
salaried employee.
165:
You're no longer chained to this
place. You're free to go wherever
you please now, young lady.
168:
Hmmm, in that case, I wanna check
out Alk and Nimbus' place.
172: With all of you, of course!
176:
By all means! You're all welcome in
Starview Village. I'm sure you'll make
lots of friends there too.
181:
Nyahaha! Then it sounds like our
next task is secured!
184:
The Special Equipment Defense
Force is going on an extended
vacation!
